<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf68d9aa2-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10708"><num value="10708">§ 10708.</num><heading> Sale of property</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A district court of the United States may direct the sale of any part of the property of a deceased seaman. Proceeds of the sale shall be held as wages of the seaman are held.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf68d9aa3-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/574">97 Stat. 574</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
